From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Michael Verrilli <msv@pobox.com>
Date: Mon, 4 May 2026 03:45:10 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] ggml: add CUDA kernels and ops for TurboQuant KV compression

Adds six GGML ops backed by CUDA kernels for compressed KV cache:

  GGML_OP_TQ_ENCODE         encode K to packed N-bit + scale
  GGML_OP_TQ_ENCODE_V       encode V (per-cell scalar quant)
  GGML_OP_TQ_ENCODE_KV      combined K+V encode
  GGML_OP_TQ_DEQUANT        reconstruct f16 K
  GGML_OP_TQ_DEQUANT_KV     back-to-back K and V dequant
  GGML_OP_TQ_FLASH_ATTN_EXT fused flash attention with inline K/V decode

The CPU backend rejects all six via supports_op so the scheduler keeps
them on GPU. Kernels compile under both nvcc and hipcc; on AMD they
require wave32 (RDNA), gated on the Go side. The fused flash-attention
kernel covers head dims 64, 128, and 256; other dims fall back to the
dequant-then-stock-FA path.

Pascal cc 6.1 (Tesla P40, GTX 9xx) is special-cased: smaller block size
and a pre-loaded shared-memory Q tile to avoid the divergent shuffle
pattern that would otherwise trigger on the older warp-shuffle path.

Reference: TurboQuant arXiv:2504.19874.
